project_announced_description: This Rural Developmentinvestment will be used tofinance the purchase of assetsof a small townlumber company and hardware storein two locations: Atoka, Okla. and Hugo, Okla.The demand for lumber and hardware supplies in the two rural communitiescontinues to rise.Timber Hardware Supplymeets the demand and offers a personable customer serviceexperienceforits contractors and customers. The only competitor in the areais a chain franchise.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE NATIVE AMERICAN GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Transportation and Warehousing (48-49)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct and develop a "multi-purpose makerspace type building" which is for the emerging aviation industry and advanced technology initiatives activity of today; a modern version of a business incubator. This facility will help to support and enable growth in our emerging aviation and advanced technology initiatives. This facility will be for organizations to utilize during research, testing, development, and evaluation of its current and next generation technologies.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP-MAND ENERGY EFF IMPROV GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help with energy efficiency improvements with the purchase and installation of LED lighting throughout its store. Diamond Attachments LLC is an existing business in Atoka, Okla. that manufactures high quality heavy equipment attachments. This project will realize $6,323 per year in savings and will replace 68,727 kWh per year, which is enough electricity to power six homes.

funding_code: CF 2019 DISASTER GRANT - TORNADOES FLOODS OTHER
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase 150 laptops and two vehicles for Tushka Public Schools. The laptops will be used by students for distance learning. The vehicle purchase will include a large truck for meal deliveries to students and a smaller truck to serve as its technical support/teacher vehicle. Prior to purchasing these vehicles, school staff used their personal vehicles to perform these services for its students.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
naics_description: OTHER FIRE/RESCUE & PUBLIC SAFETY RELATED SERVICES
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to update the security system and cameras in the Atoka County law enforcement building. The county will also purchase eight tactical vests to replace the older versions currently worn by the officers. This investment will improve the safety of the officers and enhance its ability to provide public safety to the citizens of Atoka County and the City of Atoka.

funding_code: CF 2019 DISASTER GRANT - TORNADOES FLOODS OTHER
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
naics_description: RESCUE AND AMBULANCE SERVICE - EQUIPMENT BUILDING
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase two fully equipped ambulances. Atoka County Emergency Medical Services is currently using ambulances that are worn out or in need of repair. The new ambulances will allow Atoka County Emergency Medical Services to provide improved services to its customer as well as expand services to include communities that they have not been able to serve. The citizens of Atoka County and the surrounding rural areas will benefit from this investment.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a pickup truck for the Rock Creek Public School Agricultural Department. The old pickup is 14 years old and has more than 271,000 miles on it. The pickup will be used to transport students to FFA events, contests, livestock shows and provides the FFA advisor transportation to check students projects for class. The pickup will be used to promote the AG program at Rock Creek and will provide a dependable vehicle to pull its stock trailers. This pickup will insure safe transportation of staff and students to agriculture events.

This project will allow Boswell Public Schools to improve school safety for staff and students.

funding_code: PERSISTENT POVERTY CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined

Solar panels will be purchased and installed to power part of the campus. They will also purchase three heat and air units. This investment will allow Boswell Public Schools to be energy efficient, save money for the district, and provide a better facility to serve the students and employees attending Boswell Public Schools.

funding_code: PERSISTENT POVERTY (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make water system improvements for the Hugo Municipal Authority. The project is for upgrades, rehabilitation and replacement of equipment, construction of a new clearwell at the treatment plant site, new raw water intake, and new elevated water storage tank. In 2018 the project was initially awarded a Rural Development loan of $9,481,000 and grant of $1,229,000. After bids were opened, the cost had increased significantly. Hugo Municipal Authority has been issued a Notice of Violations from theOklahoma Department of Environmental Quality. Once the project is complete, the violations will be corrected. The customers of Hugo Municipal Authority, including two rural water districts, will benefit from this project.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development guarantee loan investment will provide financing for a new United States Department of Agricultureinspected beef cattle harvesting and processing plant in Thomas, Oklahoma.At full production, South Canadian Meats LLC anticipates the capability of harvesting over 100 head of cattle weekly. The products offered will be aged and sourced as verified specialty meats.The plant will provide employment opportunitiesin this small community in Custer County.

funding_code: INTERMEDIARY RELENDING PROGRAM
naics_industry_sector: Finance and Insurance (52)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used toassist and financially support at least six rural businesses in rural Weatherford, Custer, Canadian, Grady, Blaine, and Caddo Counties. The purpose of the Southwest Intermediary Finance Team (SWIFT) program is to increase economic activity and employment in southwest Oklahomas rural communities, especially disadvantaged and remote communities.Over half of SWIFTs loans have been made to borrowers in Caddo County, which has a median household income below 80 percentof the statewide non-metropolitan median household income and a Native American Population of 24 percent. SWIFT loan recipients will contribute funds derived from the IRP in the amount of at least 25 percentof the total project cost; 10 percentof the total project cost must be in cash. Thus, SWIFTs participation in IRP fund projects will be limited to 75 percent, up to $150,000. Each SWIFT applicant will be required to fund at least 10 percentof the total project cost withits own cash; the remaining 15 percentof the funding gap may come from other funding sources.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase meat processing and packaging equipment that the city of Thomas willlease to South Canadian Meats, a new processing business in Thomas, Oklahoma. South Canadian Meats is a custom meat processing operation that will focus on selling beef directly to the consumer as well as provide custom processing services for area cattle producers. This investment is creating quality jobs and coordinating with the Southwest Oklahoma Comprehensive Economic Developments strategy to build on the strengths of the regions agriculture products.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Real Estate and Rental and Leasing (53)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development loan investment will finance the renovation of a commercial building in rural Enid, Oklahoma. The building was recently purchased. After renovations are completed, space in the building will be leased to multiple small businesses which will develop the rural economy. funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase flour milling equipment. Oklahoma WheatGrowers Association Inc. will lease the equipmentto Chisholm Trail Milling in Enid, Oklahoma. The equipment will be used to mill wheat from area producers in an effort to best vertically integrate the farming, milling, and baking operations. Chisholm Trail Millings goal is to redefine the relationship between bakers and wheat. They will repatriate the terroir and integrity of wheat to flour by controlling the entire process from the dirt to the oven. Their process will include research into new outlets and uses for wheat to expand existing markets as well as develop new markets. Chisholm Trail Milling will connect the dots between flavor and ingredients.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to finance the purchase of a rural community hospital in Pauls Valley, Okla. Pauls Valley General Hospital closed in November 2018 after more than four decades of operations. In January 2019 Southern Plains Medical Center Inc. acquired and incorporatedthreeprimary care clinics, including Pauls Valley Medical Center,as part of its network of physicians and clinics. The 75,000 square foot hospital facility is licensed for 65 beds. The first floor contains the lobby, Administration,admissions,Emergency Department, Imaging, Medical Laboratory, and the Surgery department. On thesecond floor there aretwo wings of patient rooms: 23 private and 21 semi-private. The original hospital was built in 1979 withadditions ofa new Emergency Room, Operating Room, Radiology, and Laboratoryin 2016.

funding_code: ECONOMIC IMPACT INITIATIVE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Elmore City-Pernell Public Schoolsmakeimprovements for their school.They will install a fence around the playground, constructtwo concrete slabs for a basketball court and other activities, and purchase playground equipment and band instruments.This project will allow Elmore City-Pernell Public Schools to provide a safe place for children to play, promote physical exercise, and engage more students in music education.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a 71-passenger 2022school bus for the Elmore City-Pernell school district.This school districtismore than 225 square miles. Due to the district size,theyrequire additionalbuses to providetransportation for students and their families. Thisnew bus will serve as a route bus, providing safe transportation for the students attending Elmore City-Pernell Public Schools.

funding_code: B&I CORONAVIRUS AID, RELIEF AND ECONOMIC SECURITY ACT GUARANTEED LOANS
naics_industry_sector: Mining, Quarrying, and Oil and Gas Extraction (21)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide working capital for a stone quarry located in Poteau, Okla. DTD Caldwell Enterprises Inc., doing business as Bluebird Stone, was formed in 2006 to mine flagstone in eastern Oklahoma. Today, Bluebird has more than 35,000 acres available to mine with 10 mining operations and is the largest producer of Oklahoma flagstone. Bluebird sells exclusively throughout the central United States to distributors only.

DTD Caldwell Enterprises Inc., doing business as Bluebird Stone, was formed in 2006 to mine flagstone in eastern Oklahoma. Today, Bluebird has more than 35,000 acres available to mine with 10 mining operations and they are the largest producer of Oklahoma flagstone. Bluebird sells exclusively throughout the central United States to distributors only.

funding_code: ECONOMIC IMPACT INITIATIVE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
naics_description: OTHER PUBLIC BUILDING & IMPROVEMENT RELATED SERVICES
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase equipment to create a Sensory Ethnography Lab for Bokoshe Public Schools. The sensory equipment will be used with theme-based activities, to support Sensory Ethnography Lab concepts including stress management, communication skills, and social engagement. This sensory room will offer a sensory rich learning environment with opportunities for touch, sight, sound and more.

funding_code: CF 2019 DISASTER GRANT - TORNADOES FLOODS OTHER
naics_industry_sector: Transportation and Warehousing (48-49)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a 71-passenger bus, a 12-passenger van and learning equipment for the Talihina Public School to serve its students in a pandemic environment. The bus will replace an older bus and the van will be used for food delivery to virtual students. They are purchasing 250 laptops and 100 tablets to facilitate virtual learning for students. This project will benefit the students attending school in Talihina.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
naics_description: OTHER PUBLIC BUILDING & IMPROVEMENT RELATED SERVICES
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist the Bokoshe Public Schools purchase appliances for its kitchen. The purchase is comprised of a commercial planetary floor mixer including beaters and bowls, a gas range/griddle, a proofing cabinet, and a walk-in combination cooler. The new appliances will be replacing outdated equipment. This investment will benefit the people of Bokoshe

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
naics_description: OTHER PUBLIC BUILDING & IMPROVEMENT RELATED SERVICES
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a tractor and related equipment for the Bokoshe Public Schools. The tractor and the front end loader, box blade and cutter will be used for school grounds maintenance, FFA projects, and other school-wide projects. This project will allow Bokoshe Public Schools to maintain school grounds, baseball and softball fields.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase aschool marquee and twosunshades for the Wister Public Schools. The marquee will increase communication and provide a positive form of communication within the community and the school district.The shades will be mounted to cover the outside lunch tables and benchesat both the middle school and high school.The sunshades will provide protection from the weather for the students and teachers attending Wister Public Schools.This project will allow Wister Public Schools to better serve and protect their students and staff and communicate school events with the Wister community.

This investmentwill benefitthe residents within the city of Guthrie.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a structural fire engine for the city of Guthrie Fire Department. This new fire engine will replace one of the departments three engines ranging from model years 1991 to 2001. The new engine is equipped with a four-man custom built cab, 1,500-gallon-per-minute firefighting pump, 750-gallon water tank, aluminum firefighting body, ladders and hoses. This investment will increase the ability of the city of Guthrie Fire Department to provide safety services to its citizens. This project will benefit the residents within the city of Guthrie.

naics_industry_sector: Professional, Scientific, and Technical Services (54)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used tofundexpansion of the Fairview Industrial Park. An additional 16 acres will be developed for small and emerging businesses. Thisinvestment provides the city of Fairview the opportunityto work with new businesses and business expansions through these Industrial Park sites. This investment facilitates thecontinuing revitalization of Fairview, Oklahoma.

borrower_name: JOHN'S FARM OKLAHOMA FAMILY FARM LLC
funding_code: LOCAL AGRICULTURE MARKET RESOURCE PROGRAM (LAMP) VALUE-ADDED PRODUCER GRANTS - COVID
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will provide working capital funds to Johns Farm Oklahoma Family Farm LLC for processing, delivery, marketing and brand awareness of Johns Farm Beef, an organic, grass-finished beef sold farm-gate to doorstep to consumers. This investment will help expand their customer base by 54 percent. The global pandemic initiated their pilot idea to direct ship Johns Farm Beef, farm-gate to doorstep, to meet consumers mounting interest in convenient access to value-added beef. The results of this will be two-fold, satisfied consumers and economic stability for Johns Farm which leads to economic benefits to individuals, the community and the state.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase two new police vehicles for the townof Salina, Oklahoma. Salinahasfive full-time and three reservepolice officers. Theyhavesix vehicles that are high mileage andin poor mechanical shape.In the last 12 months,Salina has spent approximately $30,000 in repairs on their police vehicles.This grant will help the town purchase two fully equipped F150 police responders. This investment will save thetaxpayers money and will increase the safety for the residents of Salina.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development guarantee loan investment will refinance a combination of existing loans while also providing additional funds for working capital for Johnson Enterprise Holding Co ET ALin Muskogee, Oklahoma.The borrower is a real estate lessor who will lease a grocery store facility as well as a small shopping center.The development will provide access to a designated underserved food access location, according to United States Department of Agriculture Economic Research Service. Additionally, this investment will support the rural workforce creating local jobs and developing the rural economy.

funding_code: LAMP VALUE ADDED PRODUCER GRANT MANDATORY
naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide Pecan Creek Winery LLC with working capital to rebrand and market its current value-added products. Pecan Creek is a six-year-old fruit and grape-growing operation and bonded winery, it it also one of the fewer than 10 wineries in Oklahoma that grows most of its own grapes instead ofstarting with barrels of South American grape concentrate. The winery will engage with a food and beverage industry brand consultant to help develop a consistent brand and appealing message. Its initial labels have been in use since 2015 and are inconsistent in appearance and make little distinction between their whimsical fruit wines and their more serious, classic dry wines. Pecan Creek will work with a consultant to revamp its labels to help better market its prestigious wines while also expanding its sales regionally into Colorado, Texas, and Missouri.

funding_code: CF 2019 DISASTER GRANT - TORNADOES FLOODS OTHER
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make parking lot improvementsforFort Gibson Public Schools. These improvements will doublethe size of the current school parking lot, creating 42 new parking spaces. Theparking lot addition includes a new service drive for school pickup/drop off of students.Currently student pickup after school results in blocking traffic, emergency vehicles and first responders. The new service drive willprevent blocking ofa public street and access for emergency services.The new add on will also be used as an emergency heliport. These improvements will benefit the students and citizens in the Fort Gibson area.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a Kubota tractor for Committed to Build and Beautify Taft, Inc. This investmentwill benefit the people of Taft and the local surrounding area.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide technical assistance. Neighbors Building Neighborhoods of Muskogee, Inc (NBN) will providetechnical assistance to20 small rural Oklahoma towns, communities, and non-profit organizations in eightOklahoma counties.NBNs training and technical assistance will provide training meetingswith the leadership of each ultimate recipient and will provide guidance on the types of eligible projects for the agencys Community Facilities Loan and Grant program. As part of NBNs role in training and technical assistance, NBN will assist with preparing applicants for what will be expected of them in becoming an ultimate recipient.Many small rural towns, communities, and nonprofits areresource poor and operate onsmall budgetswith limited or no paid staff.NBN proposes to offer their services and resourcesfor grant writing, planning, and hiringarchitects andengineers to help these small towns and communities identify their most pressing needs.

funding_code: LAMP VALUE ADDED PRODUCER GRANT MANDATORY
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide working capital to increase the processing and marketing of an Oklahoma certified beef product produced by Far Away Ranch LLC. In 2020, the cattle market inconsistencies were exacerbated as COVID-19 forced shutdowns, resulting in a shortage of packaged beef and inflated prices at grocery stores. Far Away Ranch adjusted its business model to improve the vagaries of the cattle market, increase revenue from operations, and provide consumers with a higher quality locally produced product. The ranch is operating and producing grass-fed, grain-finished Black Angus beef cattle with an established feeding process resulting in a premium natural-flavored tender beef product. The ranch will expand its customer base to local grocery stores, cafes, and restaurants; a market segment the ranch has not previously entered. This will substantially increase the raw commodities available for use in the production and distribution of their packaged, private label beef products.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct a32 mile Fiber-to-the Premises system to benefit 86 residents and 4businesses in the Little River Ranch, Pushmataha County, Oklahoma service area. Subscribers will have access to service up to 1 Gbps, expanding access to economic, educational, health care, and public safety opportunities. A Community Center will be provided in an existing building where residents can access the Internet free of charge for at least two years.

funding_code: PERSISTENT POVERTY COMMUNITY CONNECT GRANT BROADBAND TELECOM GRANT FY 2001
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct a 34-mile Fiber-to-the Premises system to benefit198 residents and 2 businesses in the Watson, McCurtain County, Oklahomaservice area. Subscribers will have access to service up to 1 Gbps, expanding access to economic, educational, health care, and public safety opportunities. A Community Center will be provided in an existing building where residents can access the Internet free of charge for at least two years.

funding_code: DLT GRANTS - CARES ACT - EDUCATIONAL
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to establish a distance learning network linking Cameron University with 28 rural school districts, in 10 counties in Oklahoma. The schools will deliver Science, Technology, Engineering and Math (STEM) and college courses to high school juniors and seniors.

funding_code: DLT GRANTS - CARES ACT - EDUCATIONAL
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to establish a distance learning program for students and adults in five school districts in Atoka and Coal counties in southeast Oklahoma. The districts will partner with a local career technology center to increase course offerings. Interactive video rooms will be built on all end-user sites to enable the districts to offer professional development and school courses for students. The technology will also enable teachers and students to stay connected, especially in the event of a school shutdown due to circumstances like the COVID-19 pandemic.

funding_code: DISTANCE LEARNING- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide telecommunications equipment to connect Mid-America Christian University in Cleveland County, Oklahoma with rural high schools in Grady and Adair Counties. College-Level Education and Access for Rural Schools (CLEARS) is an expansion of a successful Mid-America Christian University (MACU) Distance Learning and Telemedicine (DLT) grant project that is currently being implemented called ATOMS (Access to Online Math and Science). The overall goal for CLEARS is to increase concurrent college enrollment and to provide content support for students and teachers at the CLEARS school districts. The project will deliver subject matter content for teachers and students in grades 11-12 in two remote, rural school districts via synchronous distance learning. Over the course of the three year project period, approximately 800 students and residents will be served.

funding_code: DISTANCE LEARNING- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This USDA investment will be used to replace Oklahoma Public School Resource Centers aging videoconferencing equipment and introduce new videoconferencing equipment at the hub and end user sites. The project will use technology to connect students and teachers across long distances. Distance learning services will be offered via a fixed-site project and will provide approximately 700 students and 50 teachers with fixed site interactive video systems and touch panels to create an environment for sharing and collaboration between project sites. Distance learning capabilities for 2,000 rural citizens will be impacted by the enhancement.

funding_code: DISTANCE LEARNING- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to establish a distance learning program in three school districts in Creek and Okmulgee counties. The system will enable schools to expand course offerings, including Science, Technology, Engineering and Math (STEM) and provide professional development classes. The grant will help the districts to adapt to the COVID-19 pandemic and a post-pandemic world by funding classroom equipment, student devices and connectivity to enable students to join classes from home. Videoconferencing and interactive display panels will enable students to explore career interests and take virtual field trips for cultural and educational enrichment. This project is also expected to help Oklahomas rural schools recruit and retain teachers.

funding_code: TELEMEDICINE- GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help the Southwestern Oklahoma State University (SWOSU) College of Pharmacy Rural Health Center buy equipment to implement telemedicine in LeFlore County and western Oklahoma counties over the next three years. In the first year of the grant, Southwestern Oklahoma State University will collaborate with Eastern Oklahoma Memorial Center (EOMC) in Poteau (LeFlore County), in order to put telemedicine equipment in six rural public-school locations in LeFlore County. In the second and third years of the grant, Southwestern Oklahoma State University goal is to serve 18 rural schools in western Oklahoma counties. Overall the project will bring telemedicine access to an estimated 50,000 residents and over 12,000 students.

The company has diversified by providing multiple services and equipment rental in Oklahomaand Texas. funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Real Estate and Rental and Leasing (53)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investmentloan will be used to help finance the construction of two office warehouse buildings in Harrah, Okla. These office warehouse buildings will consist of 72 units that will be leased out to upscale shopping stores, restaurants, and offices. Harrah, Okla. is part of a rapidly growing community being near Oklahoma City and the Kickapoo turnpike. The office warehouses will support the shopping, dining, and business needs of this community as they continue to grow.

funding_code: LOCAL AGRICULTURE MARKET RESOURCE PROGRAM (LAMP) VALUE-ADDED PRODUCER GRANTS - COVID
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will provide working capital to Icehouse Urban Creamery to assist with processing expenses, supply purchases, and marketing of their new value-added product, cheese. Visitors of the creamery will be able to watch cheese being processed, view a live video streaming of cows being milked or grazing on pasture, and taste a wide selection of cheese and other dairy products. The storefront will also include take-away food made on-site, including cheesecakes and quiches made with the cheese, as well as refrigerated and frozen food from other local farms. The store will also include an old-time lunch counter for a quick grilled cheese sandwich or a scoop of mac n cheese.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase furniture and equipment for the College of the Muscogee Nations new educational facility and exhibit hall located on their campus in Okmulgee, Oklahoma. The college is a 1994 tribal land-grant institutionproviding employment and higher education courses, which result in an Associate Degree and/or Certificates. The college has673 staff members and students, primarily Native American, that residewithin an eight-county region of central Oklahoma. The college has been limited in classroom space dedicated for Science, Technology, Engineering and Math (STEM) related activities and classes. Many of the students have expressed a need for a variety of classes to choose from.This project will allow the college to enhance its educational opportunities and increase its capabilities of their learning platforms, with additional office space, classrooms, lab workspace and exhibit/lecture hall.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will provide working capital funds to The Egg Packer LLC for the processing, packaging, and marketing of pasture-raised, free range and cage free eggs. The Egg Packer LLC, the sole egg processing facility in Oklahoma, will take eggs from independent producers and convert those eggs to meet Food and Drug Administrationstandards. They will link the independent producers of raw eggs with distributors, grocery stores and restaurants in a manner that will increase their profitability and competitiveness.

funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) SOLID WASTE GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used by Oklahoma State University (OSU)to provide technical assistance, training and educationto rural areas of Oklahoma aboutSolid Waste Management (SWM) andthe economic and ecological importance of establishing and implementing SWM programs in their areas.This grant proposes to continue OSUs community volunteer program and provision of workshops and training opportunities to interested communities on waste management, non-point source pollution (water resource training), and law enforcement trainings.

funding_code: LAMP VALUE ADDED PRODUCER GRANT MANDATORY
naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide Stobaugh Wine Group LLC withworking capital funds to launch a new brand of wine. Funds will be used for the packaging, branding, marketing and market expansion of the newly labeled wines. Stobaugh will be launching "Farm Girl Wines," a new collection of wines that are designed for distribution in convenience stores, grocery stores, and liquor stores as well as restaurants and bars. This wine will consist of local cannedandscrew cap wines to add a wider appeal to convenience and box stores.Local fruits will be processed in the style of their fifth-generation winemaking family and made into their blends that have been proven successful over the last 16 years of business. With a push to distribute in the new location types, they aim toincrease their visibility and gainnew customers that have never had their products.

borrower_name: PITTSBURG PUBLIC SCHOOLS, DISTRICT NO. I-063
funding_code: CF 2019 DISASTER GRANT - TORNADOES FLOODS OTHER
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
naics_description: COMMERCIAL AND INDUSTRIAL MACHINERY AND EQUIPMENT (EXCEPT AUTOMOTIVE AND ELECTRONIC) REPAIR AND MAINTENANCE
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make improvements to the Pittsburg Public School. The improvements include insulating the gym roof, replacing the kitchen and cafeteria flooring, replacing 116 exterior windows, and replacing the heat/air system. Purchases for the school include 170 student desks, 225 chairs, intercom/phone system, and a security system including card readers for doors. This project will benefit the faculty, staff and students in the town of Pittsburg.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make water system improvements for the Haileyville Public Works Authority. The water system consists of approximately 17 miles of water line. Much of the water line is cast iron and in poor condition which results in leaks and broken pipes. This improvement project is to replace water lines, gate valves, install fire hydrants, add service connections, chlorine booster station and air vacuum releases. After the proposed project is completed, water losses will be reduced, low pressure areas will improve, fire flow requirements will be improved, and operation and maintenance costs will be reduced. The project will improve service to the customers of Haileyville Public Works Authority.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make improvements to the water system at Hartshorne, Okla. The Hartshorne Public Works Authority water system is under an Oklahoma Department of Environmental Quality Consent Order for violations within the water distribution system. This improvement project will address the violations. Improvements include replacing 42 miles of water distribution lines to alleviate low pressure areas, satisfy fire flow requirements, decrease water losses, and decrease operations and management costs. This investment will benefit the water customers of the Hartshorne Public Works Authority.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) ECWAG - APPROPRIATED $1,000,000 LIMIT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make repairs to the Pittsburg Public Works Authority raw water intake. In February 2021 Oklahoma experienced an extendedperiod of single digit and sub-zero temperatures. The raw water intakewas damaged during this period and haslimited thetreatment plant capacityto produce water. This investment will be used toreplace the intake screen and intake pipe.

funding_code: LAMP VALUE ADDED PRODUCER GRANT MANDATORY
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide working capital funds to increase the processing, marketing and advertising for Callison Ranch Beef LLC. It will also allow them to add new value-added products such as convenience meals, protein snacks and pet snacks for its local customers. The beef is ranch raised,processed and soldto local customers. Callison Ranch Beef willutilize a commercial kitchen to create the economical and convenient prepared food products and meal kits for humans and pets while adding value to less desirable beef cuts, incorporating local farm goods, meeting the need for healthy convenient food options and creating jobs in the rural area. Callison Ranch Beef will also offer cooking classes demonstrating easy family dinner recipes using local food sources, nutritional information, food safety and healthy eating guides in a hands-on environment, especially for low-economic areas. They will host a farm to table experience on the ranch promoting ag-tourism and ag-education in an on-farm experience serving their beef products and local products.

This project will benefit the students that attend school in Clayton, Okla.

naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will provide working capital funds to allow SemCo Meat Processing to increase their processing numbers and market their locally raised and processed beef to area consumers. Within the last year, consumer demand for locally produced and processed meat has increased dramatically. Due to this demand they lost access to consistent processing for their live cattle. This investment will allow them to take out the middle man and complete the whole process on their own. After processing, the funds will be spent introducing the product to the local community. It will be used to pay a sales and marketing coordinator to promote the companys beef. SemCos beef will be sold directly to the consumers from the plants retail store.

funding_code: (LOAN ONLY) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make water system distribution improvements for Sequoyah County Water Authority. They plan to replacefour pump stations, with one being enlarged, and to construct 89,000 linear feetof 12 inch waterline andreplace two miles of 3inch waterline with8 inch waterline. They willreplace a water storage tank with a new 330,000 gallon tank, install a new 220,000 gallon tank, and rehabilitate an existing tank. These improvements will provide some low-pressure areas in the water distribution system,allowing them to serve more of their own customers with water, reduce their water purchases by 70 percent and improve their operating expenses.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to finance the working capital for an oilfield rental company in Duncan, Okla. BK Equipment offers a variety of services and products to serve almost any need for most onshore oil and gas companies. They also provide fabrication services including hydraulic hose assembly, cement fracturing hose assemblies, blowout preventer hose fabrication, and much more. This loan guarantee will benefit this rural community with the additional of employment opportunities.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help the City of Comanche construct two, fully accessible, restrooms at two separate cultural event locations. borrower_name: ASSOCIATION OF SOUTH CENTRAL OKLAHOMA GOVERNMENTS
funding_code: CF TAT GRANT (SECTION 6006)
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide financing to the Associationof South Central Oklahoma Governments (ASCOG) to serve as a technical assistance provider to 15 small rural Oklahoma towns, communities, and non-profit organizations infour Oklahoma counties. ASCOG will provide training and guidance to theleadership of each ultimate recipienton the types ofprojects eligible for funding under the agencys Community Facilities Loan and Grant program. As part of ASCOGs role in training and technical assistance, theywillprepare applicants for what will be expected of them in becoming an ultimate recipient.Most small rural towns, communities, and nonprofits areresource poor,operate on small budgets, andhave limited or no paid staff. ASCOG proposes to offer their provider services and resources for grant writing, planning, and hiringarchitects and engineers to help these small towns and communities identify their most pressing needs.

naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to establish a revolving fund to make small loans to eligible water and wastewater systems in rural areas nationwide.

funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) TAT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to establish a pipeline of highly skilled water workers that will protect USDAs investment in rural America and improve service to rural customers. The National Rural Water Association has designed this proposal to deliver measurable results by enhancing quality of life by creating jobs in rural America; advancing technological innovation at small water and wastewater systems; creating economic development opportunities in eligible communities; and helping rural communities become strong, modernized, safe and sustainable.

funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) TAT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used towill employ twenty-five certified Energy Efficiency Technicians to perform on-site assessments, calculate the scope of potential improvements in efficiencies and cost savings, and assist in developing action plans for implementation. The National Rural Water Association will develop energy efficiency assessments on 750systems, identify 125 previously identified utility systems to provide support and assistance while serving as a liaison with all applicable groups to encourage the development and implementation of a plan of action to reduce energy costs by 10 percent or greater, develop and conduct two webinars and provide a uniform energy efficiency assessment report that will provide the outcomes and data collected during assessments.

funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) TAT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development Investment will be used to support the sound development of rural communities and growth of our economy; enhance the sustainability of utility system governance, management, and operations through project development and the delivery of the Sustainable Utility Management program, and hands-on technical assistance in all 50 states. Also, enhance sustainability, reduce costs, and provide technical assistance and training to modernize and upgrade infrastructure to prioritize climate change solutions, continue to target and prioritize TAT toward the smallest communities with the lowest incomes and poor sanitation, emphasizing designated Opportunity Zones and areas where at least 20 percent of the population is living in poverty; create nine new positions dedicated to providing assistance to projects located in Substantially Underserved Trust Areas; provide education and implementation support that assists utility systems in addressing emerging contaminants of concern, including per- and polyfluoroalkyl substances (PFAS) chemicals; maintain a highly competent technical field staff of wastewater technicians who deliver quality services; and provide emergency planning, rapid response, and recovery assistance during disasters.

funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) TAT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to support the sound development of rural communities and growth of our economy; enhance the sustainability of utility system governance, management, and operations through project development and the delivery of the Sustainable Utility Management program, and hands-on technical assistance in all 50 states. Efforts will enhance sustainability, reduce costs, and provide technical assistance and training to modernize and upgrade infrastructure to prioritize climate change solutions, continue to target and prioritize technical assistance and training (TAT) toward the smallest communities with the lowest incomes and poor sanitation, emphasizing designated Opportunity Zones and areas where at least 20 percent of the population is living in poverty; create nine new positions dedicated to providing assistance to projects located in Substantially Underserved Trust Areas; provide education and implementation support that assists utility systems in addressing emerging contaminants of concern, including per- and polyfluoroalkyl substances (PFAS) chemicals; maintain a highly competent technical field staff of wastewater technicians who deliver quality services; and provide emergency planning, rapid response, and recovery assistance during disasters.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Real Estate and Rental and Leasing (53)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to finance the construction of two retail buildings thatwill include upscale retail shopping and two office warehouse buildings in Glenpool, Okla. The two retail buildings will be a total of 13,500 square feet and the two office warehouse buildings are 10,500 square feet each.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Retail Trade (44-45)
project_announced_description: This Rural Developmentinvestment will be used tofinance the business expansion of Floyds RV. Floyds RV is a recreational vehicledealer that currently operates in Norman, Oklahoma and will expand to Glenpool, Oklahoma.The facility will consist of a 37,000square footfacility with 332 RV parking spaces, 92 customer parking spaces, and a 10-bay service area with a wash bay.

funding_code: HIGHER BLENDS INFRASTRUCTURE INCENTIVE PROGRAM GRANTS - MANDATORY
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to create infrastructure to expand the sales and use of renewable fuels.Magellan Pipeline Company LP will install a 10,000-barrel storage tank with piping, pumps, gauging, manways tank insertion heater and insulation, and small biodiesel mechanical building at a distribution facility in Brookline, Missouri. It also will install a 25,000-barrel storage tank, piping, pumps, gauging, manways, tank insertion heater and insulation, andsmall biodiesel mechanical building at a location in Kansas City, Kansas. This project is expected to increase the amount of biodiesel sold by 223,661,458 gallons per year.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist in the purchase of 10 acres, which will be used for a community garden. KCDS currently serves bags of groceries to approximately 1,800 individuals weekly. KCDS plans to use the 10 acres to create a fully functional community garden. This will increase inventory and lower the cost of providing fresh food to the community. This project will benefit the residents within the towns of Inola and Wagoner.

This purchase will benefit the people of Stilwell and Adair County.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)

These vehicles will be used to replace high mileage vehicles that are beyond their life expectancy and require increased and costly maintenance. This project will supply vehicles equipped with emergency lights and sirens and be used to provide 24-hour police protection and law enforcement services to the city of Anadarko with a population of about 6,700.

project_name: PURCHASE AND INSTALL A NEW GEN
funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a generator to provide power to the nursing home in Wakita, Oklahoma during power outages. Wakita is a rural community at the end of a power line, and the last community to have power restored during these outages. This project will ensure the community will have continuous power during power outage events, primarily caused by weather. The installation of the generator will have an automatic transfer switch that allows the generator to automatically kick on when needed. This will provide power to the patients, cook staff, and employees to help provide needed care, regardless of weather.

naics_industry_sector: Construction (23)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help England Construction Inc., an industrial construction company in Waurika, Oklahoma, install a 15 kilowatt (kW) wind turbine. This project is expected to save $3,140.90 per year. It will generate 31,409 kilowatt hours (kWh) per year.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
naics_description: OFFICES OF PHYSICIANS (EXCEPT MENTAL HEALTH SPECIALISTS)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist with modifications to the Ringling Family Care Clinic. The projects primary purpose is to renovate the space for larger care spaces, updated heating, ventilation and air conditioning (HVAC) equipment and install additional health safety measures for team members, acute care patients, and patients with airborne viruses such as COVID-19. They will also be making its exam rooms Americans with Disability Act compliant with larger care spaces. The HVAC system will include ultraviolet light scrubber that cleans the air on every return. This project will allow Ringling Family Care Clinic to better serve the rural community and provide more advanced services to the community during a pandemic.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) ECWAG - APPROPRIATED $1,000,000 LIMIT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to replace the damaged transmission line coming from the water treatment plant to one of the water towers. The damages, caused by several days of sub-zero temperatures in February included several breaks and cracks in the line which compromised the lines ability to consistently deliver water. The new line will be replaced with a ten-inch line with the appropriate valves and tie-ins to the tower and at the treatment plant to provide safe and sanitary water to the community. They have a population of 3,034 in the town of Tishomingo, Oklahoma.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) ECWAG - APPROPRIATED $150,000 LIMIT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to reimburse the applicant for emergency repairs to the water system caused by extreme freezing temperatures during a winter storm. Power was lost for several hours and when it was restored, damage was discovered to the in-line meters and the telemetry system. The valves, pumps, and pressure gauges had frozen at the plant, tower, and booster system which were repaired during the emergency and partially reimbursed by FEMA. The SCADA system was also damaged and will be replaced, and filters at the water treatment plant will be repaired.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to restructure debt, purchase equipment, and provide working capital for a sod farm in Spiro, Oklahoma. Two States Sod Farm grows, processes, distributes, and installs grass sod (bermuda, fescue, and zoysia grasses) throughout Arkansas and eastern Oklahoma. The farm operates more than 1,500 acres of land.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to renovate an existing emergency room and waiting area. The current status of the emergency room layout is not built to handle the high volume of visits. It does not allow for ease of use for the doctors, nurses or patients. The renovation will rearrange the nurses station for better visibility throughout the emergency room and the restroom will be relocated and updated with American with Disabilities Act upgrades. The emergency room will be expanded into the current Intensive Care Unit. This update will allow the hospital to serve the over 15,000 patients who visit the emergency room per year.

naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to renovate the old city hall and masonic lodge. The building was acting as a community center, but is currently unusable due to needing extensive repairs. Once repaired, the three-story building will be used to teach drama, music, dance, and fine arts. There will be mental therapy services offered for children with various mental health issues. The renovation will also bring the building up to current Americans with Disabilities Act compliance.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) SEARCH GRANTS WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to complete an Engineering Report, Master Planning Study, Hydraulic Analysis and Water Age Study for LeFlore County Rural Water District #17. This project will help identify those issues and help with planning a future project. The customers of the District will benefit from this project.

naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to install a bulk oxygen system, repair the medical vacuum system and purchase computer equipment for the enhancement of telehealth services. These improvements will expand the health care offerings and ability to respond to COVID-19 mental health issues and complications. The bulk oxygen system, repaired medical vacuum system and computer equipment will allow the Prague Healthcare Authority to respond to future pandemic surges and offer improved health care options.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Real Estate and Rental and Leasing (53)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help the city of Guthrie construct a pop-up shop park in Guthries Downtown Historic District. The site was previously home to two beautiful historic buildings that were tragically destroyed in a fire and this project will turn its loss into something vibrant for its citizens and downtown economy. It will serve the community as a gathering space and a retail incubator. This project will bring in six new small businesses to their community. It will create a simpler path for small retailers to begin production and selling goods out of a storefront in hopes they can grow into a traditional brick-and-mortar store.

funding_code: PERSISTENT POVERTY (LOAN ONLY) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to rehabilitate the Idabel Public Works Authority water treatment plant. These improvements will alleviate health and sanitary violations. Improvements include new valving, crane and intake screens at the intake structure, a pretreatment basin with aeration, dual rapid mix basin, splitter box, clarifier mechanisms and covers, improved chemical feed, filter media as well as two additional filters, new filter covers, and rehabilitation of the filter controls. Modifications to the filter gallery piping, and a 1.4 million-gallon finished water storage tank with transfer pumps will also be made. The project includes high service and backwash pumps, a chemical/high service building, chlorine building, rehabilitation of a lagoon, a new decant lift station, along with electrical, SCADA, and piping at the water treatment plant. The treatment plant monitoring, controls and process optimization will also be rehabilitated.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Accommodation and Food Services (72)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist Tiger Mountain RV LLC (TMRV) with construction costs. TMRV was formed for the purpose of constructing and operating an RV and horse motel on Interstate 40 near Henryetta, Oklahoma. The RV Park is scheduled to open during the summer of 2022. Tiger Mountain RVs location and variety of amenities is expected to enjoy strong demand from RV owners, both with and without horses. Due to its convenient location near the Interstate 40 & US Highway 75 cross section it is expected to quickly build a strong customer base.

naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to allow Neighbors Building Neighborhoods (NBN) of Muskogee, Inc., to serve as a technical assistance provider, to 19 small rural Oklahoma towns, communities, and non-profit organizations in four Oklahoma counties. This project will enable NBN to provide training and technical assistance, and to provide guidance on the types of eligible projects for the agencys program. As part of NBNs role in training and technical assistance, NBN will assist with preparing applicants for what will be expected of them in ultimately becoming a recipient.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be usedfor the Hunger Relief Expansion Initiative for the Noble County Family Young Mens Christian Association (YMCA). A community center will be provided as part of the project where residents can access the Internet free of charge for at least two years.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to deploy a fiber-to-the-premises network to connect 1,529 people,90 farms, 37 businesses and six educational facilities to high-speed internet in Jefferson County, Oklahoma. Terral Telephone Company will make high-speed internet affordable by participating in the FCCs Affordable Connectivity Program. This project will serve socially vulnerable communities in Jefferson County and the Chickasaw Oklahoma Tribal Statistical Area.

funding_code: PILOT BROADBAND GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to deploy a fiber-to-the-premises network. This network will connect 200 people, 16 businesses and one educational facility to high-speed internet in Choctaw and McCurtain counties in Oklahoma.Valliant Telephone Company Inc. will make high-speed internet affordable by implementing the FCCs Affordable Connectivity and Lifeline programs, and offering four internet packages.This project will serve the Choctaw Oklahoma Tribal Statistical Area and socially vulnerable communities in McCurtain County.

program: Telecommunications Infrastructure Loans and Loan Guarantees (TELE)
borrower_name: The Hinton Telephone Company of Hinton,
funding_code: TELE SECTION 305 VARIABLE TELE TREASURY RATE - LOAN PERSISTENT POVERTY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to install 60 miles of fiber-to-the-premises (FTTP) and associated electronics in five exchanges. Loan funds will be used to replace a soft-switch, add a new warehouse, remodel a warehouse, and purchase new construction equipment. The fiber deployment to the densely populated communities of The Hinton Telephone Company exchanges will help offer improved broadband service to more than 1,600 customers, with a 5th year projection of 3,348 subscribers total across voice, video, and broadband.

naics_industry_sector: Wholesale Trade (42)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to establish inpatient dialysis with the purchase of two dialysis machines at the Pawhuska Hospital. This is a service that will benefit the people of Pawhuska, Oklahoma, a distressed community. The hospital had an outside contract that was terminated during the COVID-19 pandemic and now will utilize their own staff to provide this service and by doing so it will limit the traffic of outside parties and reduce the threat of the spread of COVID. This will also allow the facility the ability to respond to future pandemic surges and improved healthcare options.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Energy Audits and Renewable Energy Development Grants
funding_code: REAP ENERGY AUDIT RECIPIENT
naics_industry_sector: Professional, Scientific, and Technical Services (54)
naics_description: OTHER SCIENTIFIC AND TECHNICAL CONSULTING SERVICES
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to establish a statewide Energy Audit Program for agriculture producers and rural small businesses. The program will focus on rural and underserved populations. The program will be established and operated under the Biosystems and Agricultural Engineering Department of the Division of Agricultural Sciences and Natural Resources at Oklahoma State University. This new center will provide assessments/audits to small rural businesses and agriculture producers helping to reduce their energy waste while increasing productivity.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Arts, Entertainment, and Recreation (71)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase and install a 85 kilowatt (kW) solar array for Ultimate Air Stillwater LLC, a locally owned rural small business in Stillwater, Oklahoma. The project generates 119,946 kilowatt hours (kWh) (87 percent of the companys energy use) per year, which is enough energy to power 11 homes.

naics_industry_sector: Real Estate and Rental and Leasing (53)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist in the transfer, assumption and rehabilitation of Eagle Crest Apartments, a multifamily housing complex in Cushing. The project consists of two one-bedroom, 42 two-bedroom, seven three-bedroom, and five four-bedroom units. All units will undergo significant rehabilitation and improve the living conditions for all current and future tenants.

funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) SOLID WASTE GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide technical assistance, training, and education to rural areas of Oklahoma in the field of Solid Waste Management (SWM), and to help participants understand the economic and ecological importance of establishing and implementing SWM programs in their areas. This grant proposes to continue OSUscommunity volunteer program and provision of workshops and training opportunities to interested communities on waste management, non-point source pollution (water resource training), and law enforcement trainings.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Construction (23)
naics_description: OIL AND GAS PIPELINE AND RELATED STRUCTURES CONSTRUCTION
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist GLSJ Services LLC purchase Horizon Pipeline & Construction, via stock purchase. Horizon was established in 2016 and installs new pipelines, pipeline fabrication, install meter stations and processing facilities, lease road construction for the oil production industry. GLSJ is a new business that will be purchasing the stock of this existing company.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Wholesale Trade (42)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to implement a telehealth program for McAlester Regional Hospital.McAlester Regional Healthcare Authority (MRHC) willcreate a telehealth program to provide a safe alternative way for patients to see doctors during the pandemic.The implementation of virtual visits will provide an alternative to coming into the hospital or clinic, while decreasing no show appointments. This is especially needed due to Covid and the desire to keep patients out of the hospital and clinics unless medically necessaryand at the same timeproviding access tohealthcare for those in rural areas. MRHC will use the grant funds to purchase 127 computers, program license and to hire a trainer/coordinator. Thecoordinator will provide technical support and training for the doctors and staff.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Wholesale Trade (42)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to expand and remodel the current laboratory within the existing footprint at McAlester Regional Hospital. It will allow the hospital to have a positive impact on patient care by deterring patients from traveling to another area, or possibly going without care, due to limited access of services in the area. Upon completion of project, McAlester Regional will be able to provide a higher volume of services to southeast Oklahoma and the surrounding communities and manage another potential pandemic surge without delays. An increased square footage will allow more patients to be seen with less wait time, and an expanded number of tests will be provided in a central location, including those related to SARS Co V-2 antigen and antibody tests, therapeutic drug monitoring and immunoassay tests.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Wholesale Trade (42)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase hospital laboratory equipment. McAlester Regional Healthcare Authority has two chemical testing instruments that are outdated. The pandemic has increased the volume of testing required by the hospital. The new equipment, including an analyzer with automation system and two chemistry systems, will account for 126,000 chemistry tests. The new equipment will allow the hospital to test for SARS CoV-2 antigen and antibodies, metabolic chemistries, therapeutic drug monitoring and immunoassay test.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide additional financing for water system improvements. These improvements include 8,000 linear feet of new water line, 3,700 linear feet of water line replacements, cleaning and repainting a standpipe, rehabilitating a clearwell and a clarifier at the water treatment plant, adding a liquid chlorine system, and new automatic read water meters. Previous funding includes an $836,000 loan and $365,000 grant from Rural Development. This funding will be used with a new $50,000 contribution from the Choctaw Nation/Indian Health Service.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WATER ONLY

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) ECWAG - APPROPRIATED $150,000 LIMIT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to replace a water line that burst during the February 2021 extended period of sub-zero temperatures in Oklahoma. The water line was located inside a concrete drainage structure. The drainage structure had to be demolished to access the water line. The new water line is being installed in a location north of the drainage structure to avoid future problems. This project will benefit the customers of the Haileyville Public Works Authority.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide additional funding for water system improvements. These improvements include replacing four pump stations, with one being enlarged, constructing 89,000 L.F of 12" waterline, upgrading two miles of three-inch to eight-inch waterline, replacing a tank with a new 330,000 gallon tank, installing a new 220,000 gallon tank, and rehabilitating a tank. These improvements will improve some low-pressure areas as well as allow them to serve more of their own customers with water, reducing their water purchases by 70 percent and improving their operating expenses. Previous funding includes a $12,358,000 loan from Rural Development.

funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) TAT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to create a career pathway for water workers through the National Apprenticeship/Workforce Development Program, to enhance quality of life, create jobs, and promote economic development opportunities in rural America while improving water and wastewater infrastructure across the country. Activities will be provided to ensure workforce development. The specific goals and objectives for this proposal are: (1) establish a nationally recognized credential that certifies occupational proficiency, is portable, and provides a pathway to economic opportunity; (2) build a qualified workforce that will protect USDAs investment in rural America, and improve service to rural customers; (3) develop a systematic approach to training that ensures highly skilled employees for rural water and wastewater utilities, with a focus on technology and innovation; (4) create and maintain a nationwide clearinghouse for training materials and resources; (5) establish nationwide water industry training courses and certifications; (6) enhance workforce participation in rural America, with a special focus on women, youth and veterans; (7) enhance retention of water workers in small and rural communities through the proven earn-and-learn training model of apprenticeship; and, (8) increase emergency preparedness and resiliency to natural disasters in RUS-eligible communities through a well-trained workforce.

borrower_name: Rural Water Sewer Gas & Solid Waste Management District Number 9 Wagoner County Oklahoma
funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make water system improvements for Wagoner Countys rural water users. This investment, combined with IHS grant assistance and an applicant contribution will serve a population of 4,344 residents. Upgrades to the water treatment plant include replacing clarifier units, electrical improvements, installing a Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition system, replacing raw water pumps, installing additional floats on the raw water structure, relocating a chemical feed system, rehabbing the filter gallery and other associated filter work, and cleaning the clear well. Improvements outside of the plant upgrades include water tower/storage tank improvements, replacing lake crossings and the booster pump station, and installing an Automatic Meter Readers (AMR) system. The installation of the AMR system will help the district reduce operation costs and reduce water loss, making the water system more sustainable. Improvements will also help alleviate a health and safety concern and improve water pressure and further reduce water loss.

funding_code: GUARANTEED B&I 3% FEE LOAN
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
naics_description: ASSISTED LIVING FACILITIES FOR THE ELDERLY

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
naics_description: RESCUE AND AMBULANCE SERVICE - EQUIPMENT BUILDING
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used purchase 51 new Automated External Defibrillators (AEDs) and an ambulance. The life-saving devices will be located in law enforcement vehicles, schools, libraries and county buildings throughout the county. Atoka County EMS will also purchase 51 pads for the AEDs, as this will allow Atoka EMS the ability to respond to future pandemic surges and provide improved health care options. The ambulance purchase will solidify the fleet assuring the service area the best chance of rapid response and transport. The Atoka EMS is the only ambulance service available in the county to provide prehospital emergency medical care. At the present time, Atoka EMS has two quality first line ambulances and the secondary ambulance has accumulated many miles due to the increased call volume over the time of the peak of the COVID-19 pandemic. When an ambulance is out of service, Atoka EMS needs to have quality secondary ambulances to turn to for response. Without quality ambulances in their fleet, their response times and delivery of rapid patient care are decreased.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase two fully equipped ambulances, a bariatric stretcher, a first responder SUV and a video laryngoscope that will be used to better equip the team members to perform the task of patient care during an emergency. Primary care access, trainings, and communications is a pressing challenge in rural communities in Southeastern Oklahoma. Choctaw County had patient transport numbers of 2,987 total runs in 2022. Some of the challenges faced during the COVID-19 Pandemic was proper training of emergency medical services personnel, reliable radio communications with health care professionals and other services due to the lack of digital radio communication in their fleet and electronic health information exchange with telehealth capabilities.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase tablets for medical reporting, digital radios, mobiles, truck, and base station for communications and Training Mannequins that will be used to better equip team members to perform the task of patient care during an emergency. Primary care access, trainings, and communications is a pressing challenge in rural communities in Southeastern Oklahoma. Choctaw County had 2,987 patient transport runs last year. Some of the challenges faced during the Covid-19 Pandemic were proper training of Emergency Medical Services personnel, reliable radio communications with health care professionals and other services due to the lack of digital radio communication in their fleet and electronic health information exchange with telehealth capabilities. Primary care access, trainings, and communications is a pressing challenge in rural communities in Southeastern Oklahoma. Choctaw County had 2,987 patient transport runs last year. Some of the challenges faced during the Covid-19 Pandemic were proper training of Emergency Medical Services (EMS) personnel, reliable radio communications with healthcare professionals and other services due to the lack of digital radio communication in their fleet and electronic health information exchange with telehealth capabilities.

naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
naics_description: RESCUE AND AMBULANCE SERVICE - EQUIPMENT BUILDING
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase two ambulances and two new patient lifts for ambulances. Johnston County Emergency Medical Services currently has two ambulances with more than 200,000 miles and they are at the end of their shelf life. The power lifts will place cots into and out of ambulances, reducing spinal loads and risk of cumulative injuries. This investment will lower maintenance costs, improve response times and increase the safety for EMS employees and the residents of Johnston County.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide funding for the Carney Public Utilities Authoritys (CPUA) wastewater collection system. The authority will replace all sewer lines, manholes and service taps within the collection system. Additionally, the authority will install one 5 Horsepower (HP) surface aerator and installing one 35KW generator and gas line. By eliminating the sources of inflow and infiltration, the CPUA will reduce the amount of water entering the lagoons. This will result in an increased detention time along with additional aeration will reduce Biochemical Oxygen Demand 5 (BOD5) concentration and loading discharging into Bell Cow Creek. This wastewater improvement project will benefit the citizens of the town of Carney, Oklahoma.
